Welcome to the world of Big Data!

Spark is a "Distributed Computing Engine." Unlike a traditional database that runs on one powerful server, Spark breaks a massive task into tiny pieces and distributes them across a cluster of computers.
The Three Pillars of Spark:
1.	In-Memory Processing: Unlike Hadoop MapReduce (which writes to disk after every step), Spark keeps data in RAM. This makes it up to 100x faster for certain tasks.
2.	Lazy Evaluation: Spark doesn't do any work until it absolutely has to. It builds a "plan" (the DAG) and only executes it when you ask for a result.
3.	Fault Tolerance: If one of your Docker containers crashes, Spark knows exactly how to re-compute the missing data because it remembers the "lineage" (the steps taken to create that data).
