2. The Programming Model-
When you write Spark code, you are essentially dealing with two types of operations:
A. Transformations (The Plan)
These are operations that tell Spark how to change the data.
•	Examples: filter(), map(), groupBy(), select().
•	Behavior: Nothing happens when you run these. Spark just adds them to its "To-Do" list.
B. Actions (The Execution)
These are commands that tell Spark "Give me the result now."
•	Examples: count(), collect(), show(), save().
•	Behavior: This triggers the cluster to start working. 
