3. First Project
the best way to start is by comparing a SQL query to a Spark DataFrame operation.
The Task: Find the average salary of employees per department.
The SQL Way :
SQL
SELECT dept_id, AVG(salary) 
FROM employees 
GROUP BY dept_id;
The Spark Scala Way (The New Way):
Scala>>val df = spark.read.json("employees.json")
df.groupBy("dept_id")
  .avg("salary") 
  .show()
